pH_red_median = wine[wine["type"]=="red"]["pH"].median()
pH_white_median = wine[wine["type"]=="white"]["pH"].median()

sns.displot(wine, x="pH", hue="type", palette="rocket_r",element="step")
plt.axvline(x=3.45, color="maroon", linestyle ="--", alpha=.5)
plt.axvline(x=pH_red_median, color="maroon", alpha=.8)

from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn import preprocessing
import numpy as np

scaled_wine = preprocessing.scale(wine.iloc[:, 1:])
pca = PCA()
pca.fit(scaled_wine)
pca_data = pca.transform(scaled_wine)
In [ ]:
per_var = np.round(pca.explained_variance_ratio_* 100, decimals=1)
labels = ['PC' + str(x) for x in range(1,len(per_var)+1)]

plt.bar(x=range(1,len(per_var)+1), height=per_var.cumsum(), tick_label=labels)
plt.ylabel("Percentage of Variance Explained")
plt.xlabel("Principal Component")
plt.show()

wine_notype = wine.iloc[:, 1:]


for i in range(5):
    loading_score = pd.Series(pca.components_[i], index=wine_notype.columns.to_list())
    sorted_loading_scores = loading_score.abs().sort_values(ascending=False)

    top_10_genes = sorted_loading_scores[:10].index.values
    print("PC" + str(i+1) +":")
    print(loading_score[top_10_genes])
